{"questionId":"25627","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the series <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>p</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the case where the series is geometric.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence or otherwise, show that the series is convergent.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">since,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>p</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">since,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>p</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>⇒</mo></math>&nbsp;the geometric series converges.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><br><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> instead of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>.<br>Award <em><strong>R0</strong> </em>if both values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> not considered.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25627","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ1.10a.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence or otherwise, show that the series is convergent.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.7—Laws of exponents and logs","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Sum of infinite geo sequence"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}